Event Name: Life After Bucknell Optimizing Your Career
Image Filename: Life After Bucknell Optimizing Your Career.jpg
Description: Join Bucknell Alumnus Doug Palmer ‘80, as he discusses how to effectively optimize your career in the first 10 years after Bucknell. With a focus in the tech and engineering world, Doug has fostered employee mentoring activities at Motorola, Google, and ARRIOS and will provide the best advice on how to structure your work life, build your connections and more so that you can realize your dream career.

The Office of International Student Services would like to invite you to join us for this year’s international and multicultural showcase event, A Trip Around the World. This will be our 4th year hosting this exciting event that not only highlights the broad diversity of students represented on our campus, but also students’ interests in world cultures and global topics. And there will be unique foods to sample! In years past we have had upwards of 20 countries represented and over 600 students in attendance. Do not miss out on the fun!

Event Name: LGBTQ Isseus in the Workplace - Alumni Career Panel
Description: This lunchtime panel discussion will examine the career paths of Bucknell alumni who can speak about LGBTQ issues in the workplace. Come hear their advice and perspectives as they discuss their experiences and offer advice and suggestions. The conversation will also include a question and answer period. Lunch is provided.
